The skin rash treatment market can be segmented by various factors, with the product type being a crucial one. Topical ointments are popular for their localized application and rapid relief, making them a common choice among patients. Oral medications provide systemic relief and are often prescribed for more severe or widespread skin conditions. Injectable treatments, though less common, are used in cases where other forms of medication have proven ineffective. Distribution channels play a significant role in the accessibility of these treatments, with hospital pharmacies being the primary source for prescription medications, while retail and online pharmacies cater to over-the-counter products. When considering the indication for treatment, allergic reactions, dermatitis, and psoriasis are among the most prevalent conditions that drive the demand for effective skin rash treatments.

